    "In addition, when the target can be defined as a singleton (→ Features), observers can adopt a singleton-detection mode (→ Templates and strategies) and purposefully search for any visually salient stimulus (Bacon & Egeth, 1994; Leber & Egeth, 2006) or for a salient stimulus in a particular feature dimension (dimensionweighting account; Found & Müller, 1996; Liesefeld et al., 2022; Liesefeld & Müller, 2019; Müller et al., 1995)."
